By Mr. Mark, a petition (accompanied by bill, Senate, No. 2420) of Paul W. Mark and James C.
Arena-DeRosa for legislation to reduce emissions from the journey a truck takes to deliver or
pick up goods. Transportation.
The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act reducing truck trips and emissions.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 1 of Chapter 90 of the General Laws, as so appearing in the 2022
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by adding the following in alphabetical order to the list of
3 definitions:
4 “Truck-trailer unit”, a motor unit composed of a motor vehicle designed to carry a load
5 and having a minimum of three axles, such as a dump truck, log truck, or other truck, paired with
6 a trailer having a minimum of two axles.
7 SECTION 2. Section 30A of Chapter 85 of the General Laws, as so appearing in the 2022
8 official edition, is hereby amended by replacing “motor vehicle, trailer, semi-trailer or semi-
9 trailer unit” with “motor vehicle, trailer, semi-trailer, semi-trailer unit, or truck-trailer unit” in
10 each instance of this section.
